        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">Reviewed by a QuickBooks Payroll ProAdvisor &middot; independent, no reseller incentive</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="qbpye-credentials">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Certified by Intuit &middot; Payroll, Online (L2), Desktop, Enterprise</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stat-row">
      {%- for s in credStats %}
      <div><div class="stat__value">{{ s.value }}</div><div class="stat__label">{{ s.label }}</div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbpye-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Year-end payroll, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbpye-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Year-end payroll, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbpye-deadlines">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The key deadlines</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Six deadlines that drive year-end work.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Year-end payroll is fundamentally deadline-driven. Each of the six below carries real penalties for missed timing and shapes the engagement schedule.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for d in deadlines %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbpye-categories">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What year-end includes</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Six categories of work, every engagement.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Year-end work spans more than form generation. The full scope below is what a proper engagement covers &mdash; skip any one and you create downstream issues that compound through February and March.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in categories %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ c.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbpye-mistakes">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common year-end mistakes</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Six items that don&rsquo;t surface in regular payroll cycles.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The most consequential year-end mistakes cluster around items that never come up in routine payroll. They surface only at year-end &mdash; or worse, only when employees find discrepancies on personal returns in March.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for m in mistakes %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ m.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ m.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbpye-pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fixed-fee, scoped by complexity.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Year-end pricing scales with employee count, adjustment complexity, and the multi-state factor. Engagement timing matters: <strong>booking by mid-December</strong> means pre-year-end reconciliation and adjustments are handled before December&rsquo;s final payroll; <strong>booking in January</strong> means working against the January 31 deadline with less buffer.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for p in pricing %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ p.eyebrow | safe }}</p>
        <h3>{{ p.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbpye-boundaries">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What we don&rsquo;t do</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The honest scope boundaries.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Year-end payroll sits adjacent to business income-tax work but doesn&rsquo;t overlap it. Three boundaries we maintain cleanly:</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for b in boundaries %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ b.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ b.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbpye-cycle">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The engagement cycle</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">When work happens, across the cycle.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Year-end isn&rsquo;t one phase. The work splits across roughly four phases between late November and mid-March. Earlier engagement means cleaner outcomes; later engagement means working under tighter deadlines.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in cycle %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        {%- if c.num %}<p class="section__eyebrow">{{ c.num }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbpye-routing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Your situation</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where are you with year-end payroll?</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for b in routing %}
      <a class="buyer-card" href="{{ b.href }}"><p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ b.opener | safe }}</p><p class="buyer-card__body">{{ b.body | safe }}</p><span class="buyer-card__cta">{{ b.cta | safe }}</span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbpye-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who performs the work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified ProAdvisor. Deadline-driven. Coordinated with your CPA.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Year-end is the most consequential payroll cycle of the year. Wrong W-2s mean employees file personal returns on wrong data; missed adjustments mean W-2c amendments through April; missed state filings mean penalties. Every TechBrot year-end engagement is delivered by a Certified Payroll ProAdvisor on a deadline-driven schedule with fixed-fee scoping &mdash; not hourly billing against unpredictable seasonal demand.</p>
      <p>We handle the payroll-side year-end work. <strong>Your CPA handles the business income-tax filing</strong> (Form 1120, 1065, Schedule C) &mdash; we coordinate to ensure the payroll-side data flowing to those returns is correct. No commission on Intuit products, no affiliate revenue. You can <a href="/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/">meet the ProAdvisor team</a> or read our <a href="/trust/">trust &amp; methodology standards</a>. Independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="qbpye-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Year-end payroll questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask about year-end payroll.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="qbpye-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="qbpye-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-14</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-14</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-14 &middot; QuickBooks Payroll ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="qbpye-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related references</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Other payroll resources.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
